## Async/Await Requirements

### Functions Using `await` Must Be `async`

Any function that uses `await` must be declared as `async`:

```typescript
// ✅ Good
async function handleSubmit() {
  isSubmitting = true;
  await update();
  isSubmitting = false;
}

async function fetchData(): Promise<Data> {
  const result = await api.get('/data');
  return result;
}

// ❌ Bad: Missing async keyword
function handleSubmit() {
  isSubmitting = true;
  await update(); // Error: 'await' expressions are only allowed within async functions
  isSubmitting = false;
}

function fetchData(): Promise<Data> {
  const result = await api.get('/data'); // Error: 'await' expressions are only allowed within async functions
  return result;
}
```

### Arrow Functions with `await`

Arrow functions using `await` must also be `async`:

```typescript
// ✅ Good
const handleClick = async () => {
  await tracker.track('event', {}, session, page);
};

use:enhance={() => {
  return async ({ update }) => {
    await update();
  };
}}

// ❌ Bad: Missing async keyword
const handleClick = () => {
  await tracker.track('event', {}, session, page); // Error
};

use:enhance={() => {
  return ({ update }) => {
    await update(); // Error
  };
}}
```
